            <thetext>The inspector uses settings for its workings, which is all fine and good, but 
the naming has gone wrong. As layed out in the documentation (s.URL), and 
recommended to all users, settings for an application or library shall be named 
starting with the library&#39;s name space. The inspector should follow this rule 
and rename some of the settings its using, e.g.:

&quot;qx.inspector.selenium.core&quot; -&gt; &quot;inspector.selenium.core&quot;
&quot;qx.inspector.selenium.extensions&quot; -&gt; &quot;inspector.selenium.extensions&quot;
etc.

These settings have nothing to do with the framework, but are 
application-specific. It is wrong to think every setting has to start with 
&#39;qx&#39;, just because it is a setting, and our own apps should not enforce this 
misconception.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
